# Implementation workflow

## Autonomy

- Do not ask unnecessary questions if the answer is in the code, `AGENTS.md`, or issues.
- Use reasonable defaults; ask only for real product decisions.
- Run commands, checks, and tests yourself ‚Äî do not stop with ‚Äúask the user‚Äù.

## Bun

- **Bun only** (`bun install`, `bun run`, `bun test`) ‚Äî not npm/yarn/pnpm.

## Code

- **No legacy** ‚Äî when changing stack, remove old deps, files, compose services in the same change.
- **Minimal diff** ‚Äî do not touch unrelated code.
- **Commits** ‚Äî only when the user explicitly asks.

## `.env`

- **Read and edit** `.env` yourself when needed for dev (keys, `DATABASE_URL`, `TELEGRAM_LOGIN_*`, `BASE_URL`).
- **Do not commit** `.env` ‚Äî only `.env.example` in git, no secrets.
- Shell does not load `.env` automatically ‚Üí `bun --env-file=.env test` or `bun run dev` (Nuxt loads it).
- Dev HTTPS: `make tunnel` (cloudflared). **Not localtunnel.** See [`.docs/technical-design.md`](.docs/technical-design.md).

## DB migrations

- Schema changes **only** via incremental migrations: `db:generate` ‚Üí `db:migrate`.
- **Forbidden:** `DROP SCHEMA`, truncate, rebuilding `0000_init.sql` to ‚Äúrefresh‚Äù an existing DB, `db:reset` script.
- Policy: [`.docs/database-migrations.md`](.docs/database-migrations.md).

## Operator CLI

- New **manual** prod ops commands ‚Üí subcommand in `scripts/cli.ts` (`commander`), logic in `server/core/operator/` or reuse `server/` services/repos.
- Build: `bun run build:cli` ‚Üí `.output/cli.cjs`; Docker copies to `/usr/local/bin/cli`.
- Docs: `.docs/deploy.md` (Operator CLI section), for billing ‚Äî `.docs/billing-design.md`; locally `bun run cli -- ‚Ä¶`.

## Tests

When changing `server/**` ‚Äî see `unit-tests` rule (separate glob).

## Logging (`server/**`)

When changing `logger.*` in `server/**`:

- **debug** ‚Äî frequent operational trace (updates, LLM prompt/response, lookups); **info** ‚Äî rare business events (moderation outcome, webhook lifecycle).
- At `LOG_LEVEL=info`, one moderated message ‚Üí a few info lines, not step-by-step trace.
- LLM prompts/responses **debug** only; no `"Debug:"` prefix ‚Äî pick the right level.
- Policy: [`.docs/logging.md`](.docs/logging.md).

## i18n (admin UI)

When changing **user-facing UI** (`pages/`, `components/`, `layouts/`, client composables):

- Strings only via **`$t()` / `t()`** ‚Äî keys in `i18n/locales/en.json` + **parity** in `ru.json`.
- Naming: nested JSON, dot keys (`nav.bots`, `bot.chats.addChat`, `common.save`).
- Document title: `usePageTitle(() => t('page.*.documentTitle'))`; app name ‚Äî `useAppName()` (`APP_NAME` env).
- Breadcrumbs: translated `label` from `t()`, not literals.
- In locale JSON: escape literal `{user_mention}`, `@username` ‚Äî see [`.docs/i18n.md`](.docs/i18n.md).
- After locale edits: `bun test tests/unit/i18n/locale-key-parity.test.ts` + `bun run build`.
- **Do not translate:** per-bot warn/ban templates, `RULE_TEMPLATES`, API `statusMessage`, release note bodies.
- README: edit **`README.md` and `README.ru.md`** together (not the same as `i18n/locales/`).
